From 9694b1eb36a5c315b2e6e1adaf22f906a611702e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vivek Vardhan Arrabelli <vivekrao.arrabelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 01:47:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] TRUNK-6634: Run mysql-only changesets on MariaDB

MariaDB 11 dropped the "5.5.5-" version-string prefix, so Liquibase now
detects it as MariaDB rather than MySQL and silently skips changesets
declared with dbms="mysql". This left schema and core data missing on
MariaDB 11 deployments: cohort_member lost its primary-key/uuid
migration in the 2.1.x update log, scheduler_task_config uuids were
never generated before their not-null constraint, the 'System
Developer' role was never re-created, and 248 further 2.0.x changesets
plus the 1.9.x snapshot FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS toggles never ran.

Checksum-safety was verified empirically against Liquibase 4.32.0 (v8
and v9 checksum versions): editing the changeSet-level dbms attribute
or a dbms precondition does NOT change a changeset's checksum, but
adding a modifySql block DOES. The fix therefore:

- extends dbms="mysql" to dbms="mysql,mariadb" in place for 248
  changesets in liquibase-update-to-latest-2.0.x.xml, 3 in
  liquibase-update-to-latest-2.1.x.xml and the 2 FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS
  toggles in liquibase-core-data-1.9.x.xml. All raw-SQL changesets were
  audited individually for MariaDB compatibility (multi-table
  UPDATE/DELETE joins, backslash escapes, double-quoted literals,
  boolean literals - all identical semantics on MariaDB), and the three
  customChange classes involved contain only database-agnostic JDBC.

- leaves 201610042145-2.1 (cohort_member uuid backfill), 20100128-1
  (System Developer role) and 20090831-1040-scheduler_task_config
  (scheduler uuid backfill) untouched, since extending them would
  require new modifySql blocks and change their checksums; dedicated
  mariadb-only changesets (TRUNK-6634-2026-07-03-1000/-1001/-1002)
  perform the equivalent work with valueComputed="UUID()", each ordered
  before its dependent constraint. These also repair databases already
  stuck at a failed constraint: the backfill fills the missing uuids on
  the next update run.

- does NOT touch the 57 uuid backfills gated by mysql/oracle dbms
  preconditions: on MariaDB those are covered by the existing java
  fallback in changeset 20090402-1517 (GenerateUuid), which already
  special-cases mariadb.

Tests:

- ChangeSetChecksumBaselineTest pins the v8 checksums of all 718
  changesets in the three touched changelogs to a baseline generated
  from the changelogs before this change, i.e. the values stored in the
  DATABASECHANGELOG of existing production databases. Any future edit
  that would break "liquibase validate" for existing deployments now
  fails CI. It also enforces that mysql changesets include mariadb
  unless documented as mysql-only by design, and asserts repair
  changeset ordering.

- MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest covers the original four 2.1.x changesets
  from the ticket in detail.
